$ Partition the set {1..N} into two classes

given n: int(1..)

find class : matrix indexed by [int(1..n)] of int(1..2)
 
such that

and([or([class[a] != class[b]
     ,class[b] != class[c],
     class[c] != class[a]]) 
   | a: int(1..n), 
     b:int(1..n), 
     c:int(1..n), 
     a** 2 + b **2 = c**2])
